    <note>Wang(2) Lun(2) [8178] Yi(5)'s [7377] son, Yuan(2)'s [7385] grandson. His 6th generation ancestor, Hu [3956], used literary skills (wenzhang) in the service of Zhao(1) Taizu [9001] and Taizong [9002] to establish this lineage (qijia) branch of the clan in Daming, Xinxian. His great great grandfather, Dan [8153], was a chief minister of Zhenzong and moved to Kaifeng. In 1144, on a mission to Jin he was strangled to death by the Jurchen. His nephew, Zun [3985], moved to Suzhou at the beginning of the Southern Song. YLDD, 2367.14a; Lou Yue, WJ, 95.1a-16a; Yuan Xie, 22.1a-4a. CBD, 1, 157-8.</note>
